# API Design

## REST Only

Use standard HTTP verbs:

```
GET    — read
POST   — create
PATCH  — partial update
DELETE — remove
```

## Consistent Response Envelope

Every response uses the same shape:

```typescript
{
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: { code: string; message: string };
  meta?: { page?: number; total?: number; [key: string]: unknown };
}
```

## HTTP Status Codes

| Situation | Code |
|-----------|------|
| Success (read/create) | 200, 201 |
| Validation error | 400 |
| Unauthorized | 401 |
| Forbidden | 403 |
| Not found | 404 |
| Conflict (constraint violation) | 409 |
| Server error | 500 |

**Never return 200 with an error.** If the operation failed, use the appropriate 4xx/5xx code.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
return res.status(200).json({ success: false, error: 'Not found' });

// ✅ GOOD
return res.status(404).json({
  success: false,
  error: { code: 'NOT_FOUND', message: 'Asset not found' },
});
```
